RAK Properties PJSC (RAKPROP) , the developer
that built Ras  Al Khaimah â€™s first manmade islands, said third-
quarter profit dropped 55 percent after it set aside money for
impairments and as expenses rose.  Net income fell to 30.3 million dirhams from 67.5 million
dirhams a year earlier, the company said in a  statement  to the
Abu Dhabi bourse today. Impairment on available-for-sale
investments climbed to 15 million dirhams from 3.2 million
dirhams, while expenses increased to 14.4 million dirhams from
